goals.question: What is the highest and lowest CO2 level recorded?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Date')
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 levels over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['adjusted_CO2'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['adjusted_CO2'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['adjusted_CO2'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['adjusted_CO2'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['adjusted_CO2'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of adjusted CO2 levels?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Month'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Month'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce').dt.month_name()
    data = data.groupby('Month').mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['Month'], data['CO2'])
    plt.title('What is the average CO2 level per month?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['CO2'], data['adjusted_CO2'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between CO2 and adjusted CO2 levels?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('CO2')
    plt.ylabel('adjusted_CO2')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='CO2', ascending=False)
    data = data[['Date', 'CO2']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data['Date'], data['CO2'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('CO2')
    ax.axhline(y=data['CO2'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max CO2: {data["CO2"].max():.2f}')
    ax.axhline(y=data['CO2'].min(), color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'Min CO2: {data["CO2"].min():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the highest and lowest CO2 level recorded?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
